  "title": "SENIOR INTERIOR DESIGNER",
  "description": "<p>We are seeking a Senior Interior Designer to join our team and contribute to the design team. The ideal candidate will have a strong background in technical drafting, a keen eye for detail, and experience working on intricate designs. </p><p><br /></p><p>Job Responsibilities:</p><ul><li>Ideate, conceptualize, and present precise 3D design proposals.</li><li>Interpret project briefs and translate ideas into accurate visual representations.</li><li>Develop detailed 3D models of interior spaces, including furniture, finishes, and built-in carpentry.</li><li>Prepare precise technical drawings for layouts, detailed plans, and construction references.</li><li>Collaborate with internal teams (designers, production, suppliers) to ensure high-quality project execution.</li><li>Attend creative review meetings to align design direction and progress.</li><li>Maintain and update the 3D rendering & material library for efficient workflow.</li><li>Keep abreast of new 3D tools, software, and interior design trends</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Job requirement</p><ul><li>Diploma/Degree in Interior Design, Architecture or equivalent.</li><li>Minimum 5 years of relevant experience in an interior design or architectural firm.</li><li>Strong proficiency in AutoCAD is a must</li><li>Solid understanding of spatial planning, construction detailing, and materials.</li><li>Strong attention to detail and ability to deliver high-quality output consistently.</li><li>Excellent communication and teamwork skills.</li><li>Able to manage time independently and meet project deadlines.</li></ul><p>Working arrangement:</p><ul><li>4-day work week</li><li>10% of profit sharing scheme on top of basic pay</li></ul>",
